In the eastern populations workers are paler, body sculpture feebler, and the post-ocular surface of head in particular is smooth and shiny. Smaller workers often bear one pair of standing hairs on genae. This combination of characters is more frequent in the eastern populations and rare in the western ones. Some workers in nest series from Calabria and Syracusa (
Italy
) also bear this combination of characters, especially in the case of small workers.

